    <title>Software and Setup Utilities</title>
    <conbody>
        <section>
            <p>The preliminary delivery includes two <codeph>zip</codeph> files:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><codeph>CMM_server_2.0.0.zip</codeph> for installing the Monitoring Service.</li>
                <li><codeph>CMM_client_2.0.0.zip</codeph> for installing the OpenStack extensions.</li>
            </ul>
            <p>You have to extract the files to make the included files available for the installation.</p>
            <p>After extraction of <codeph>CMM_server_2.0.0.zip</codeph> the following files are available:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><codeph>CMM_server_2.0.0.images.tar</codeph></li>
                <li><codeph>docker-compose-log.yml</codeph></li>
                <li><codeph>docker-compose-metric.yml</codeph></li>
            </ul>
            <p>After extraction of <codeph>CMM_client_2.0.0.zip</codeph> the following files are available:</p>
            <ul>
                <li><codeph>log-agent-2.4.1_0.5.3.run</codeph></li>
                <li><codeph>monasca-agent-2.2.0.run</codeph></li>
                <li><codeph>monasca-ui-1.5.1.run</codeph></li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <p>The software and setup utilities are distributed in the <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> installation package on the <ph
                    conref="../../shared/product-name.xml#ProductNameTopic/Product_Abbr"
                    /> DVD. You have to mount the DVD and execute the <codeph>setup.sh</codeph> script that is provided. It extracts the utilities required for installing <ph
